# No attribution / vanity trailers

Commits and PRs must look human-authored. Never add tool, agent, or product branding.

## Forbidden on commits and PR bodies

- `Co-Authored-By:` / `Co-authored-by:` (any bot or tool)
- `Made with Cursor`, `Generated by …`, `Generated with …`
- `Signed-off-by:` unless the human author explicitly asked for DCO
- Emoji attribution lines, “AI assisted”, “via Claude/Cursor/Copilot”, etc.
- Any other Key: value git trailer that exists only to credit a tool

## Allowed

- Conventional commit subject (+ optional body explaining *why*)
- Issue workflow lines in the body: `Closes #N`, `Refs #N` (not tool credit)
- `BREAKING CHANGE:` when needed

## Examples

```text
# ❌ BAD
feat(prelude): add Task.delay

Co-Authored-By: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>
Made with Cursor
```

```text
# ✅ GOOD
feat(prelude): add Task.delay

Closes #19
```

When creating PRs with `gh pr create`, do not append product footers.

Also turn off **Cursor Settings → Agents → Attribution** (commit + PR), and run
`git config core.hooksPath .githooks` once per clone so `.githooks/prepare-commit-msg`
strips any residual injection.
